OL,3,CSculptor creates tiny golden dragon
OL,4,Csmaller than a matchstick for Lunar
OL,5,CNew Year
OL,7,FMr Wigan, 66, told the PA news agency:
OL,8,F"I did it to celebrate (Lunar New
OL,9,FYear). It can be there as a
OL,10,Fcelebration and as a symbol of
OL,11,Fstrength, resilience and
OL,12,Fdetermination."
OL,14,FThe creature is apt as the Lunar New
OL,15,FYear, which falls on February 10, will
OL,16,Fcelebrate the Year of the Dragon.
OL,18,FMr Wigan admits his latest creation is
OL,19,F"the hardest thing I've ever done" and
OL,20,Fhas no intention of recreating this
OL,21,Fpiece.
