OL,7,F"That's because I'm not working for
OL,8,Fmyself. I'm working for other people
OL,9,Fto see it."
OL,11,FHis work is so small he said he must
OL,12,Fwork between his heartbeats and
OL,13,Fcontrol his breathing to avoid any
OL,14,Fdisturbance that might ruin his work.
OL,16,F"You have to hold your breath to do
OL,17,Fit. Between your heartbeat, you're
OL,18,Fbending and twisting and you're
OL,19,Fmanipulating the shape," he said
